CXR1631_IM-0412-0001-0001.png,Frontal,"there are a few small nodular opacities in the left lung, seen on the frontal view overlying the left 6th posterior rib. lungs otherwise appear clear. no focal airspace consolidation. no overt pulmonary edema. no pleural effusion or pneumothorax. heart size and mediastinal contour are within normal limits. calcified mediastinal and hilar lymph are consistent with prior granulomatous disease. there are mild degenerative changes of the spine. few small nodular opacities in the left upper lung. these small nodules are relatively dense, suggestive of chronic granulomatous disease. comparison with an chest radiograph would be helpful to establish stability"
